<h1>Problem 1117 - 2012 IMO, P4 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Find all functions \(f:\mathbb Z\rightarrow \mathbb Z\) such that, for all integers \(a,b,c\) that satisfy \(a+b+c=0\), the following equality holds:
\[f(a)^2+f(b)^2+f(c)^2=2f(a)f(b)+2f(b)f(c)+2f(c)f(a).\]
(Here \(\mathbb{Z}\) denotes the set of integers.)</p>
